Carludovica palmata

   [4233.jpg]
   Authority Ruiz & Pavon
   Family
   Synonyms
   Common names jipijapa palm, Panama hat palm, toquilla palm, ippi-appa
   palm, palmeira jipijapa, palmeira jijipa, palmeira carludovica,
   bombonaje, bombonaca, bombonassa
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 4233

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A 1-4 m tall plant, resembling a trunkless fan-palm
   with large, fan-shaped leaves 1-4 m tall and 100-130 cm in diameter.
   USES Fibers used for panama hats and roofing material. Despite the
   name, Panama hats are mainly made in Ecuador. GROWING PERIOD Perennial.
   If the plant is grown from seed the first leaves can be harvested after
   about 7 years, if suckers are used leaves can be harvested after about
   18 months, at which stage there will be about 20-30 leaves. COMMON
   NAMES Panama hat palm, Toquilla, Palma de sombrero. FURTHER INF Panama
   hat palm is cultivated from Central America to Ecuador. (pH estimated
   by the compiler).

   Sources
   SOURCES (C. palmata Ruiz & Pav.)
   Kirby R 1963 pp 428-429 [FER, RAIN, LIG, RAIN, TEMP, DRA, USE]
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 95-96 [USE, RAIN]
   Rehm S 1991 pp 358 [USE]

